cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Reeb graphs, which are a fundamental tool in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing Reeb graphs on large data sets. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as Reeb graphs have applications in computer graphics. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper mentions image processing as one of the applications of Reeb graphs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses parallelization of topological computations.
